<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="117">
The distinctive features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 64–69" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 64 - 69. 64 - 66 Adults. 64, 65 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 64 ♀, Type, Russia, Raddefka 65 Russia, Kajmanovka 66 Lygephila vulcanea ♀, Japan 67 - 69 Female genitalia 67, 68 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 67 Russia, Raddefka, slide No. OP 1931 f 68 Russia, Kajmanovka, slide No. 0321 Matov 69 Lygephila vulcanea, Japan, slide No. OP 2442 f." pageId="10" pageNumber="117">66</figureCitation>
) are given in the works of 
<bibRefCitation author="Sviridov, AV" journalOrPublisher="Kiev" pageId="12" pageNumber="119" pagination="97 - 100" refId="B15" refString="Sviridov, AV, 1990. K tipovym materialam sovok, opisannyh F. Brikom iz Korei. In: Novosti faunistiki i sistematiki. Kiev: 97 - 100" title="K tipovym materialam sovok, opisannyh F. Brikom iz Korei." volumeTitle="Novosti faunistiki i sistematiki." year="1990">Sviridov (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kononenko, VS" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Koreana" pageId="11" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 26" refId="B4" refString="Kononenko, VS, 1996. A revised catalogue of types of the Noctuidae (Lepidoptera) described by F. Bryk (1948) from the Korean Peninsula. Insecta Koreana 13: 1 - 26" title="A revised catalogue of types of the Noctuidae (Lepidoptera) described by F. Bryk (1948) from the Korean Peninsula." volume="13" year="1996">Kononenko (1996)</bibRefCitation>
(under the names 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila mirabilis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The main external differences between the two species are found in the colouration and shape of the forewing: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is broader winged and paler in colouration, usually ochreous brown to buff coloured, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is darker, deep brown to claret brown, most often with a clearly visible violaceous shade and the forewing apex is somewhat more pointed. In the majority of the specimens the reniform stigma of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pekarsky" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Graeser" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila lupina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lupina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila lupina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is stronger, sharper, and more distinctly marked against the paler background. The female genitalia differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lygephila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lygephila vulcanea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Lygephila vulcanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 64–69" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 64 - 69. 64 - 66 Adults. 64, 65 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 64 ♀, Type, Russia, Raddefka 65 Russia, Kajmanovka 66 Lygephila vulcanea ♀, Japan 67 - 69 Female genitalia 67, 68 Lygephila lupina (= mirabilis) 67 Russia, Raddefka, slide No. OP 1931 f 68 Russia, Kajmanovka, slide No. 0321 Matov 69 Lygephila vulcanea, Japan, slide No. OP 2442 f." pageId="10" pageNumber="117">69</figureCitation>
) by the shallower incision of the posterior margin of the antrum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="117" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="117">Wingspan 44-49 mm. Head and body brownish grey; collar dark chocolate brown. Forewing brownish grey with sparse dark brown irroration; subbasal line indistinct; antemedial line arched with costal patch; reniform stigma large, dark brown, consists of 5 or 6 streak-like spots; orbicular stigma absent; postmedial and subterminal lines distinct; terminal line a row of black dots. Hindwing brownish; small discal spot present on underside; outer third dark brown; fringes as ground color.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="117">
